<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
TYPE LOCALITY. “L’Ile Saint-Dominigue”, in error according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C." box="[892,1086,223,248]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">Anderson (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, who considers Mediterranean 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,260,284]" name="Egypt" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Egypt</collectingCountry>
more probable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
DISTRIBUTION. An extensive range from 
<collectingCountry box="[610,786,295,320]" name="Western Sahara" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Western Sahara</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[840,963,295,320]" name="Mauritania" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Mauritania</collectingCountry>
through all North African countries to the Levant, S 
<collectingCountry box="[265,349,332,357]" name="Turkey" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[360,408,332,355]" name="Iraq" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, the whole Arabian Peninsula, and marginally W 
<collectingCountry box="[965,1014,332,355]" name="Iran" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,151,752]" box="[151,1032,367,392]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3342274440" box="[151,1032,367,392]" country="Iran" location="Kermanshah" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kermanshah">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry box="[349,405,368,391]" name="Iran" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[420,502,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–73. 68" captionStartId="83.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-47@83.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="FIGURES 68–73. 68. Tropiocolotes naybandensis. 69. Tropiocolotes sp. 70. Acanthodactylus blanfordii. 71. Acanthodactylus boskianus. 72. Acanthodactylus cantoris. 73. Acanthodactylus grandis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929742/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
. 
<collectingRegion box="[513,657,367,392]" country="Iran" name="Kermanshah" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Kermanshah</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[669,723,367,392]" country="Iran" name="Ilam" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Ilam</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[734,835,368,391]" country="Iran" name="Lorestan" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Lorestan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[846,1032,367,392]" country="Iran" name="Khuzestan" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Khuzestan Prov.</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
HABITAT. The first specimens reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[664,709,404,427]" name="Iran" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Iran</collectingCountry>
were collected on sandy hills covered by 
<taxonomicName box="[1189,1310,404,429]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1189,1310,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Astragalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(RastegarPouyani 1999c). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hosseinian Yousefkhani, S. S. &amp; Rastegar-Pouyani, N. &amp; Hosseinzadeh, M. S." box="[354,813,439,464]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refId="ref53926" refString="Hosseinian Yousefkhani, S. S., Rastegar-Pouyani, N. &amp; Hosseinzadeh, M. S. (2012 b) The conservation status and serious threat to Acanthodactylus boskianus (Daudin, 1802) (Sauria: Lacertidae) in Harsin, Kermanshah, Iran. Available from: http: // www. lacerta. de / AS / Artikel. php? Article = 153 (accessed 8 July 2014)" type="url" year="2012">
Hosseinian Yousefkhani 
<emphasis box="[648,711,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
(2012b)
</bibRefCitation>
reports habitat composed of gypsum and limestone deposits with deep crevices and holes. Associated with annual grasses, 
<taxonomicName authority="Benth. &amp; Hook.f., 1865 (L.)" authorityName="Benth. &amp; Hook.f., 1865 (L.)" box="[944,1069,476,501]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Amygdalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[944,1069,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Amygdalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and Graminaceae (
<bibRefCitation author="Nazarov, R. &amp; Rajabizadeh, M. &amp; Heidari, N. &amp; Faizi, H." pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="567" refId="ref60496" refString="Nazarov, R., Rajabizadeh, M., Heidari, N. &amp; Faizi, H. (2011) Geographic distribution: Acanthodactylus boskianus (Bosc's Fringe-toed Lizard). Herpetological Review, 42, 567." type="journal article" year="2011">
Nazarov 
<emphasis box="[1387,1436,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3342274336" country="Iraq" location="Ramadieh" municipality="Ramadi" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Al Anbar">
REMARKS. The only available phylogenetic study which compared 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daudin" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[903,1046,548,573]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Acanthodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="boskianus">
<emphasis box="[903,1046,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">A. boskianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens from a larger part of its immense range suggests that the species is formed by several isolated evolutionary lineages (
<bibRefCitation author="Harris, D. J. &amp; Arnold, E. N." pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="351 - 362" refId="ref52834" refString="Harris, D. J. &amp; Arnold, E. N. (2000) Elucidation of the relationships of spiny-footed lizards, Acanthodactylus spp. (Reptilia: Lacertidae) using mitochondrial DNA sequence, with comments on their biogeography and evolution. Journal of Zoology, 252, 351 - 362. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.2000. tb 00630. x" type="journal article" year="2000">Harris &amp; Arnold 2000</bibRefCitation>
). The subspecies 
<emphasis box="[418,616,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">A. b. euphraticus</emphasis>
Boulenger (
<typeStatus box="[762,812,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
locality 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C387F2FF97FFA2FF5B4FB5558FFD5C:8EB5603FFF97FFA2FC594D4E527FFD29" box="[917,1031,620,645]" country="Iraq" municipality="Ramadi" name="Ramadieh" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" stateProvince="Al Anbar">Ramadieh</location>
[= 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1063,1156,620,645]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Ramadi</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1171,1432,620,645]" country="Iraq" name="Al Anbar" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Al-Anbar Governorate</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,200,655,680]" name="Iraq" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Iraq</collectingCountry>
]) occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[330,379,656,679]" name="Iran" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Iran</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
